{
  "texts": [
    "Tool-augmented agents can access external resources to improve task performance.",
    "This mode allows agents to invoke external functionalities such as RAG [31], [67] or executors for code validation via test cases [68], [69], enabling a more informed and actionable response generation process.② Topological Structures of Agent Networks.",
    "In addition to interaction modes, communication topology plays a critical role in shaping the collaboration efficiency and scalability of multi-agent systems in IoA.",
    "As depicted in the lower part of Fig. 8, typical topological structures include chain, star, tree, and graph, which are summarized as below.• Chain.",
    "Agents are organized in a linear sequence, where each agent processes the input from its immediate predecessor and forwards the result to the next in line."
  ]
}